.TH "pdc_interrupts_init" 9 "pdc_interrupts_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdc_interrupts_init \- Initialize the interrupt configuration for a PDC and specify a threaded IRQ handler for deferred handling of interrupts outside of interrupt context.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pdc_interrupts_init
.BI "(struct pdc_state *pdcs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdcs" 12
PDC state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the interrupt mask for transmit and receive done.
Set the lazy interrupt frame count to generate an interrupt for just one pkt.
.SH "RETURN"
PDC_SUCCESS
<0 if threaded irq request fails
